Global Objects and Functions

game  
Type: Instance  
Description: The root of the game hierarchy. Represents the DataModel instance.

workspace  
Type: Instance  
Description: Represents the Workspace, containing all visible objects in the game.

Instance Methods

Instance.Name  
Type: string  
Description: Returns the name of the instance.

Instance:FindFirstChild(childName)  
Parameter: childName (string) - The name of the child to find.  
Returns: Instance or nil  
Description: Finds the first child of the instance with the given name.

Instance:FindFirstChildOfClass(className)  
Parameter: className (string) - The class name of the child to find.  
Returns: Instance or nil  
Description: Finds the first child of the instance with the given class name.

Instance:GetService(serviceName)  
Parameter: serviceName (string) - The name of the service to retrieve.  
Returns: Instance or nil  
Description: Retrieves a service by name from the instance (typically used with game).

Instance:GetFullName()  
Returns: string  
Description: Returns the full hierarchical name of the instance.

Instance:GetChildren()  
Returns: table (array of Instance)  
Description: Returns a table of all the children of the instance.

Instance:GetPlayers()  
Returns: table (array of Instance)  
Description: Returns a table of all player instances in the game.

Instance:GetDescendants()  
Returns: table (array of Instance)  
Description: Returns a table of all descendants (children, grandchildren, etc.) of the instance.

Global Functions

printl(...)  
Description: Custom implementation of the print function, outputs the provided arguments to the console or log.

wait(seconds)  
Parameter: seconds (number) - The number of seconds to wait.  
Returns: number - The actual time waited.  
Description: Pauses the execution of the script for the specified duration.

setclipboard(text)  
Parameter: text (string) - The text to copy to the clipboard.  
Description: Copies the specified text to the system clipboard.

messagebox(text)  
Parameter: text (string) - The message to display in a message box.  
Returns: number - The user's response.  
Description: Displays a message box with the specified text.

Input Functions

isrbxactive()  
Returns: boolean  
Description: Checks if Roblox is the active window.

keypress(keyCode)  
Parameter: keyCode (number) - The key code of the key to press.  
Description: Simulates a key press.

keyrelease(keyCode)  
Parameter: keyCode (number) - The key code of the key to release.  
Description: Simulates a key release.

mouse1click()  
Description: Simulates a left mouse button click.

mouse1press()  
Description: Simulates pressing the left mouse button.

mouse1release()  
Description: Simulates releasing the left mouse button.

mouse2click()  
Description: Simulates a right mouse button click.

mouse2press()  
Description: Simulates pressing the right mouse button.

mouse2release()  
Description: Simulates releasing the right mouse button.

mousescroll(delta)  
Parameter: delta (number) - The amount to scroll (positive or negative).  
Description: Simulates scrolling the mouse wheel.

mousemoverel(x, y)  
Parameters:  
x (number) - The relative x-coordinate to move the mouse.  
y (number) - The relative y-coordinate to move the mouse.  
Description: Moves the mouse cursor by the specified relative amount.

mousemoveabs(x, y)  
Parameters:  
x (number) - The absolute x-coordinate to move the mouse.  
y (number) - The absolute y-coordinate to move the mouse.  
Description: Moves the mouse cursor to the specified absolute position.

